snippet: Two U.S. hospital workers who fell ill after contact with a patient suffering from Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) have tested negative for the often-deadly virus, a Florida health official said on Wednesday....

headline.print_headline: Two Sick U.S. Hospital Workers Test Negative for MERS Virus
headline.main: Two Sick U.S. Hospital Workers Test Negative for MERS Virus

lead_paragraph: Two U.S. hospital workers who fell ill after contact with a patient suffering from Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) have tested negative for the often-deadly virus, a Florida health official said on Wednesday.
